.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRManager

fields.name: AllowRecenter
fields.summary: If true, the Reset View in the universal menu will cause the pose to be reset. This should generally be enabled for applications with a stationary position in the virtual world and will allow the View Reset command to place the person back to a predefined location (such as a cockpit seat). Set this to false if you have a locomotion system because resetting the view would effectively teleport the player to potentially invalid locations.

fields.name: capturingCameraDevice
fields.summary: The camera device for direct composition

fields.name: chromaKeyColor
fields.summary: Chroma Key Color

fields.name: chromaKeySimilarity
fields.summary: Chroma Key Similarity

fields.name: chromaKeySmoothRange
fields.summary: Chroma Key Smooth Range

fields.name: chromaKeySpillRange
fields.summary: Chroma Key Spill Range

fields.name: compositionMethod
fields.summary: Composition method

fields.name: depthQuality
fields.summary: The quality level of depth image. The lighting could be more smooth and accurate with high quality depth, but it would also be more costly in performance.

fields.name: dynamicLightingDepthVariationClampingValue
fields.summary: The maximum depth variation across the edges. Make it smaller to smooth the lighting on the edges.

fields.name: dynamicLightingSmoothFactor
fields.summary: Smooth factor in dynamic lighting. Larger is smoother

fields.name: enableAdaptiveResolution
fields.summary: If true, dynamic resolution will be enabled

fields.name: enableMixedReality
fields.summary: If true, Mixed Reality mode will be enabled

fields.name: expandMixedRealityCapturePropertySheet
fields.summary: If true, the MixedRealityCapture properties will be displayed

fields.name: extraHiddenLayers
fields.summary: Extra hidden layers

fields.name: flipCameraFrameHorizontally
fields.summary: Flip the camera frame horizontally

fields.name: flipCameraFrameVertically
fields.summary: Flip the camera frame vertically

fields.name: handPoseStateLatency
fields.summary: Delay the touch controller pose by a short duration (0 to 0.5 second) to match the physical camera latency

fields.name: maxRenderScale
fields.summary: Max RenderScale the app can reach under adaptive resolution mode ( enableAdaptiveResolution = true );

fields.name: minRenderScale
fields.summary: Min RenderScale the app can reach under adaptive resolution mode ( enableAdaptiveResolution = true );

fields.name: resetTrackerOnLoad
fields.summary: If true, each scene load will cause the head pose to reset.

fields.name: sandwichCompositionBufferedFrames
fields.summary: The number of frames are buffered in the SandWich composition. The more buffered frames, the more memory it would consume.

fields.name: sandwichCompositionRenderLatency
fields.summary: Delay the foreground / background image in the sandwich composition to match the physical camera latency. The maximum duration is sandwichCompositionBufferedFrames / {Game FPS}

fields.name: useDynamicLighting
fields.summary: Use dynamic lighting (Depth sensor required)

fields.name: useIPDInPositionTracking
fields.summary: If true, the distance between the user's eyes will affect the position of each OVRCameraRig's cameras.

fields.name: usePositionTracking
fields.summary: If true, head tracking will affect the position of each OVRCameraRig's cameras.

fields.name: useRecommendedMSAALevel
fields.summary: If true, Unity will use the optimal antialiasing level for quality/performance on the current hardware.

fields.name: useRotationTracking
fields.summary: If true, head tracking will affect the rotation of each OVRCameraRig's cameras.

fields.name: virtualGreenScreenApplyDepthCulling
fields.summary: When using a depth camera (e.g. ZED), whether to use the depth in virtual green screen culling.

fields.name: virtualGreenScreenBottomY
fields.summary: Bottom Y of virtual screen

fields.name: virtualGreenScreenDepthTolerance
fields.summary: The tolerance value (in meter) when using the virtual green screen with a depth camera. Make it bigger if the foreground objects got culled incorrectly.

fields.name: virtualGreenScreenTopY
fields.summary: Top Y of virtual screen

fields.name: virtualGreenScreenType
fields.summary: Set the current type of the virtual green screen

methods.name: Awake()
IsAdaptiveResSupportedByEngine()
methods.summary: Adaptive Resolution is based on Unity engine's renderViewportScale/eyeTextureResolutionScale feature But renderViewportScale was broken in an array of Unity engines, this function help to filter out those broken engines

methods.name: ReturnToLauncher()
methods.summary: Leaves the application/game and returns to the launcher/dashboard

methods.name: Update()

events.name: AudioInChanged
events.summary: Occurs when the active Audio In device has changed and a restart is needed.

events.name: AudioOutChanged
events.summary: Occurs when the active Audio Out device has changed and a restart is needed.

events.name: HMDMounted
events.summary: Occurs when an HMD is put on the user's head.

events.name: HMDUnmounted
events.summary: Occurs when an HMD is taken off the user's head.

properties.name: audioInId
properties.summary: Gets the audio input device identifier.

properties.name: audioOutId
properties.summary: Gets the audio output device identifier.

properties.name: boundary
properties.summary: Gets a reference to the active boundary system.

properties.name: chromatic
properties.summary: If true, chromatic de-aberration will be applied, improving the image at the cost of texture bandwidth.

properties.name: cpuLevel
properties.summary: Gets or sets the current CPU performance level (0-2). Lower performance levels save more power.

properties.name: display
properties.summary: Gets a reference to the active display.

properties.name: eyeTextureFormat
properties.summary: Gets or sets the eye texture format.

properties.name: gpuLevel
properties.summary: Gets or sets the current GPU performance level (0-2). Lower performance levels save more power.

properties.name: gpuUtilLevel
properties.summary: Gets the GPU Utilised Level (0.0 - 1.0) This feature is only supported on QCOMM-based Android devices

properties.name: gpuUtilSupported
properties.summary: Gets if the GPU Utility is supported This feature is only supported on QCOMM-based Android devices

properties.name: hasInputFocus
properties.summary: If true, the app has Input Focus.

properties.name: hasVrFocus
properties.summary: If true, the app has VR Focus.

properties.name: instance
properties.summary: Gets the singleton instance.

properties.name: isHmdPresent
properties.summary: If true, a head-mounted display is connected and present.

properties.name: isPowerSavingActive
properties.summary: If true, the CPU and GPU are currently throttled to save power and/or reduce the temperature.

properties.name: isSupportedPlatform
properties.summary: True if the current platform supports virtual reality.

properties.name: isUserPresent
properties.summary: True if the user is currently wearing the display.

properties.name: monoscopic
properties.summary: If true, both eyes will see the same image, rendered from the center eye pose, saving performance.

properties.name: profile
properties.summary: Gets the current profile, which contains information about the user's settings and body dimensions.

properties.name: tiledMultiResLevel
properties.summary: Gets or sets the tiled-based multi-resolution level This feature is only supported on QCOMM-based Android devices

properties.name: tiledMultiResSupported
properties.summary: Gets if tiled-based multi-resolution technique is supported This feature is only supported on QCOMM-based Android devices

properties.name: tracker
properties.summary: Gets a reference to the active sensor.

properties.name: trackingOriginType
properties.summary: Defines the current tracking origin type.

properties.name: vsyncCount
properties.summary: The number of expected display frames per rendered frame.
